Once you have product vision, you can start detailed requirements by 
    - Interviews
        - Identify roles whom to interview 
            - You can use snow ball technique -> you start with one user, and interview you can idetify or ask names of people who can further help
        - Interview questions
            - Write down key interview questions and could group these questions 

    - workshops

Then build initial requires like 
    - Red30 offers features 
        - search and compare food products 
        - record and view dialy diet logs 
        - Track and analyse
    - What other products to integrate with or complainances requirements 
    - What does not this offer

Then build detailed functional requirements
